This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI no longer supports it. The replacement is the **WindowInsets API** combined with edge-to-edge layout.

Here are two approaches, simplest first:

### 1. Use MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (try first)

MAUI auto-scrolls for keyboard by default on Android. If you disabled it or it's not working for your layout, make sure it's connected:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect(App.Current!.MainPage!.Handler!.PlatformView);
#endif
```

If this doesn't handle your chat layout well (it often struggles with complex layouts), use approach 2.

### 2. Listen to keyboard insets and add bottom padding

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Platform.Compatibility;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Set edge-to-edge so insets are reported properly
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.RootView!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // The bottom padding = keyboard height (or nav bar if keyboard closed)
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);

        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

### Chat page layout (simplified)

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" x:Name="Messages" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}">
        <!-- message templates -->
    </CollectionView>

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

**Approach 2 is the most reliable** for chat screens—it gives you pixel-accurate keyboard tracking and works with `CollectionView` scrolling. The key insight is replacing the old resize mode with `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` which reports the exact keyboard height.
